1709 class TestLeaks:
1710 class A:
1711 iters = 20

1713 def bound(self, *args):
1714 return 0
1715  
1716 @staticmethod
1717 def unbound(*args):
1718 return 0

1720 @pytest.mark.skipif(not HAS_REFCOUNT, reason="Python lacks refcounts")
1721 @pytest.mark.parametrize('name, incr', [
1722 ('bound', A.iters),
1723 ('unbound', 0),
1724 ])
1725 def test_frompyfunc_leaks(self, name, incr):
1726 # exposed in gh-11867 as np.vectorized, but the problem stems from
1727 # frompyfunc.
1728 # class.attribute = np.frompyfunc(<method>) creates a
1729 # reference cycle if <method> is a bound class method. It requires a
1730 # gc collection cycle to break the cycle (on CPython 3)
1731 import gc
1732 A_func = getattr(self.A, name)
1733 gc.disable()
1734 try:
1735 refcount = sys.getrefcount(A_func)
1736 for i in range(self.A.iters):
1737 a = self.A()
1738 a.f = np.frompyfunc(getattr(a, name), 1, 1)
  • F841 Local variable 'out' is assigned to but never used
1739 out = a.f(np.arange(10))
1740 a = None
1741 # A.func is part of a reference cycle if incr is non-zero
1742 assert_equal(sys.getrefcount(A_func), refcount + incr)
1743 for i in range(5):
1744 gc.collect()
1745 assert_equal(sys.getrefcount(A_func), refcount)
1746 finally:
1747 gc.enable()

2683 # Needs range of sizes to test different code paths.
2684 # size ==1 is special cased, 1 < size < 5 is linear search, and
2685 # size >= 5 goes through local search and possibly binary search.
2686 for size in range(1, 10):
2687 xp = np.arange(size, dtype=np.double)
2688 yp = np.ones(size, dtype=np.double)
2689 incpts = np.array([-1, 0, size - 1, size], dtype=np.double)
2690 decpts = incpts[::-1]
2691  
2692 incres = interp(incpts, xp, yp)
2693 decres = interp(decpts, xp, yp)
2694 inctgt = np.array([1, 1, 1, 1], dtype=float)
2695 dectgt = inctgt[::-1]
2696 assert_equal(incres, inctgt)
2697 assert_equal(decres, dectgt)
2698  
2699 incres = interp(incpts, xp, yp, left=0)
2700 decres = interp(decpts, xp, yp, left=0)
2701 inctgt = np.array([0, 1, 1, 1], dtype=float)
2702 dectgt = inctgt[::-1]
2703 assert_equal(incres, inctgt)
2704 assert_equal(decres, dectgt)
2705  
2706 incres = interp(incpts, xp, yp, right=2)
2707 decres = interp(decpts, xp, yp, right=2)
2708 inctgt = np.array([1, 1, 1, 2], dtype=float)
